import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; export default function Blog(){ const [posts, setPosts] = useState([]); useEffect(() => { fetchPosts(); }, []); const fetchPosts = async () => { try { const response = await fetch('http://localhost:8080/api/posts'); if (response.ok) { const data = await response.json(); setPosts(data); } else { console.error('Failed to fetch posts:', response.statusText); } } catch (error) { console.error('Error fetching posts:', error.message); } }; return(
